a as we know it today. By challenging the conventional wisdom that manga evolved from centuries of prior Japanese art and explaining why manga and other comics around the world share the same origin story, Comics and the Origins of Manga offers a new understanding of this increasingly influential art form.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aComic books, strips, etczJapan. 0aComic books, strips, etc.zJapan. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  acomic studies, comic, art, Japan, anime, Japanese art, Tokyo, illustrations, comic books, comic art, media studies, popular culture.40uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197882725740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978827257423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978827257/original  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK